headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; Salling of the British Bark Resolute-Her Appearance--List of Officers. Hebrew Henevolent Society--Anniversary Celebration. St. Andrew's Society--Election of Officers. Remarkable Importations.

docs.lead_paragraph: The British Discovery Bark Resolute sailed yesterday at noon, from the Brooklyn Navy Yard, under the command of Capt. 11. J. HARTSTEIN, one of the officers of the late Arctic Expedition, for Portsmouth, England, where she will be delivered into the hands of Her Majesty's government as a present from the Government of the United States.

headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; Max Triumphant--Popular Severignity at the Academy of Music. At a meeting of the Stockholders at the Academy of Music, held Tuesday evening, the following letter was read with approval:

docs.lead_paragraph: Mr. PAINE: The Directors of the Academy, increasing it to me, requested that Mr. MABRTZEK should not be employed as conductor of the orchestra. Not wishing to enter into the differences that exist between these gentlemen, I promised to go on without him. But you saw last evening that the public rose in a body to call for him, and that the newspapers have fallen upon them and me for this exclusion.

headline.main: News from Nicaragua, California and Oregon. WALKER'S POSITION STILL MORE FAVORABLE--TRADE AND MINING GOOD IN CALIFORNIA--SERIOUS INDIAN TROUBLES IN OREGON.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Steamship Tennessee, with San Juan dates to the 5th instant, has arrived here. The previous accounts of the battles of Granada and Massayn are fully confirmed. General WALKER'S position was still more favorable, and the health and spirits of the army excellent. The Transit route was in the fine condition. The ?? also brings San Francisco dates of the 12th ultimo. mo.
